- The term 'in stock' refers to items that are currently available for sale, implying their inventory status is 'In Stock'; 
- Average category price refers to the mean price of items within a specific category ordered by a customer; 
- This query presumes that the primary interest is in customers who have ordered items that are currently available, potentially for targeted marketing or inventory management purposes.

High-value customers are those who place orders with the highest total values; 
Total customer value refers to the sum of the total order values for each customer; 
Out-of-stock orders refer to orders that contain items with an 'Out of Stock' inventory status.
